1
00:00:06,083 --> 00:00:08,083
[theme music playing]

2
00:00:10,750 --> 00:00:11,791
[man 1] You got it.

3
00:00:13,375 --> 00:00:14,458
What do you think?

4
00:00:18,208 --> 00:00:19,541
[man 2] Not now. Oh, shit!

5
00:00:24,833 --> 00:00:26,666
[man 1] Let's forgive each other.

6
00:00:26,750 --> 00:00:29,750
TERROR TUESDAY: EXTREME

7
00:00:31,458 --> 00:00:32,375
[music stops]

8
00:00:32,458 --> 00:00:37,041
INSPIRED BY STORIES
SHARED ON TERROR TUESDAY

9
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:41,583
[woman 1] It's a story from Ton,
who is here to tell us about it.

10
00:00:41,666 --> 00:00:43,958
-Ton. Hello.
-[man 1] Hello, Ton.

11
00:00:44,541 --> 00:00:45,708
[Ton] Hello.

12
00:00:46,958 --> 00:00:49,625
[man 1] When did the story
you're about to tell occur?

13
00:00:50,208 --> 00:00:53,333
[Ton] It occurred around 2014 - 2015.

14
00:00:53,416 --> 00:00:57,625
And then, a series of incidents
followed in 2019.

15
00:00:57,708 --> 00:00:58,541
[woman 2] Fuck!

16
00:01:02,083 --> 00:01:04,875
-[woman 2] Help! I can't swim! Help!
-What the hell?

17
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:09,583
[woman 2 grunting]

18
00:01:10,291 --> 00:01:11,208
[woman 2 grunting]

19
00:01:12,041 --> 00:01:13,208
[woman 2] Okay.

20
00:01:14,375 --> 00:01:15,833
[man 3 grunting]

21
00:01:17,791 --> 00:01:20,250
[woman 2] Hey. Were you drowning just now?

22
00:01:20,750 --> 00:01:22,541
Drowning? I was just chilling.

23
00:01:22,625 --> 00:01:23,916
Shit.

24
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:26,250
Why did you jump in if you can't swim?

25
00:01:26,333 --> 00:01:29,333
I thought you were drowning
so I tried to save you.

26
00:01:29,416 --> 00:01:31,166
Damn, I got wet for nothing.

27
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,000
Tell me.

28
00:01:39,541 --> 00:01:40,541
Just now,

29
00:01:42,041 --> 00:01:43,583
why were you facing down?

30
00:01:44,083 --> 00:01:45,750
[woman 2] Thought you were in MV?

31
00:01:49,833 --> 00:01:51,166
Are you keen to share?

32
00:01:51,250 --> 00:01:52,708
[eerie music playing]

33
00:02:01,291 --> 00:02:06,916
EIGHT YEARS LATER

34
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:08,000
[woman 2] Nat.

35
00:02:08,083 --> 00:02:09,125
[music stops]

36
00:02:11,208 --> 00:02:12,541
What was on your mind?

37
00:02:15,958 --> 00:02:18,291
What were you thinking about just now?

38
00:02:24,625 --> 00:02:26,625
[suspenseful music playing]

39
00:02:27,500 --> 00:02:28,333
Well…

40
00:02:30,250 --> 00:02:31,625
I have a confession.

41
00:02:35,333 --> 00:02:36,291
Today

42
00:02:37,875 --> 00:02:39,000
I've been feeling…

43
00:02:44,541 --> 00:02:46,666
-like having steamed squid.
-[music stops]

44
00:02:46,750 --> 00:02:48,416
[Nat] We're already here.

45
00:02:49,083 --> 00:02:50,083
Nat.

46
00:02:50,166 --> 00:02:51,708
[playful laughing]

47
00:02:51,791 --> 00:02:52,708
Come on.

48
00:02:52,791 --> 00:02:55,125
If you want to have it, don't do that.

49
00:02:55,208 --> 00:02:56,166
You scared me.

50
00:02:56,250 --> 00:02:58,541
[woman 2] I thought it was something bad.

51
00:02:58,625 --> 00:03:00,791
You want steamed squid, right?

52
00:03:00,875 --> 00:03:02,625
At that lady's restaurant?

53
00:03:02,708 --> 00:03:03,833
Let's go then.

54
00:03:03,916 --> 00:03:05,750
-Don't forget, okay?
-Okay.

55
00:03:05,833 --> 00:03:07,583
I'll go to the loo first.

56
00:03:07,666 --> 00:03:08,916
See you at the shrine.

57
00:03:09,625 --> 00:03:10,875
[woman 2] Be quick, okay?

58
00:03:11,666 --> 00:03:14,166
-Yes, ma'am.
-[woman 2] You're being bad today.

59
00:03:14,250 --> 00:03:16,416
Your words are annoying me.

60
00:03:16,500 --> 00:03:18,583
-[Nat] I'm sorry, ma'am.
-[bells chiming]

61
00:03:25,958 --> 00:03:27,083
[sighs]

62
00:03:27,166 --> 00:03:29,083
[suspenseful music playing]

63
00:03:30,541 --> 00:03:33,250
THRILLED TO OFFER YOU
THE POSITION OF ARCHITECT.

64
00:03:33,333 --> 00:03:35,333
[bells chiming in the distance]

65
00:03:38,125 --> 00:03:39,750
[music swells]

66
00:03:40,708 --> 00:03:42,958
[bells chiming in the distance]

67
00:03:44,333 --> 00:03:46,541
[footsteps approaching]

68
00:03:48,333 --> 00:03:49,333
Praying for what?

69
00:03:49,416 --> 00:03:50,583
[music stops]

70
00:03:55,291 --> 00:03:56,250
I'm not telling.

71
00:03:59,541 --> 00:04:01,125
[bells chiming in the distance]

72
00:04:01,875 --> 00:04:02,875
Are you sure?

73
00:04:04,208 --> 00:04:05,041
Yes.

74
00:04:05,833 --> 00:04:10,291
-There, there, there!
-Hey, stop or the Goddess will choke you.

75
00:04:12,125 --> 00:04:14,125
[eerie music playing]

76
00:04:14,208 --> 00:04:16,208
[bells chiming]

77
00:04:17,041 --> 00:04:18,958
[Nat] It creeps me out every time.

78
00:04:21,500 --> 00:04:24,666
If she hears that,
she'll surely curse at you.

79
00:04:29,916 --> 00:04:31,250
[bells chiming]

80
00:04:35,208 --> 00:04:37,541
Hi, Auntie. Two sets, please.

81
00:04:38,041 --> 00:04:39,500
[woman 3] That'll be 40 baht.

82
00:04:40,208 --> 00:04:41,500
Have you been here?

83
00:04:42,125 --> 00:04:44,291
Do you know how to pray to her?

84
00:04:44,375 --> 00:04:45,208
[woman 2] Oh.

85
00:04:45,958 --> 00:04:48,500
We come here often. No worries.

86
00:04:48,583 --> 00:04:52,333
We run a villa
on the Black Hills Beach which is nearby.

87
00:04:52,833 --> 00:04:55,708
My boyfriend came here
to do a whole new project

88
00:04:55,791 --> 00:04:58,541
[woman 2] so I came from Bangkok
to have a look.

89
00:04:58,625 --> 00:05:01,208
-Um.
-[woman 2] And…

90
00:05:02,125 --> 00:05:03,458
actually,

91
00:05:04,583 --> 00:05:09,166
I'm sure I met him
because of my prayer to the Goddess.

92
00:05:09,250 --> 00:05:11,291
-[laughs] Is that so?
-[woman 2 laughs]

93
00:05:11,375 --> 00:05:12,916
How long has it been?

94
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:14,541
[woman 2] Oh, I think

95
00:05:15,208 --> 00:05:16,916
it's been almost eight years.

96
00:05:17,416 --> 00:05:19,166
It all started in college.

97
00:05:19,250 --> 00:05:22,458
Now, we're almost in our thirties.

98
00:05:22,541 --> 00:05:23,375
Yes.

99
00:05:24,333 --> 00:05:26,291
-Shall we go?
-[woman 3] Hold on.

100
00:05:26,375 --> 00:05:27,666
[ominous music playing]

101
00:05:29,416 --> 00:05:30,666
People these days

102
00:05:31,250 --> 00:05:34,000
don't really know
the background of this place.

103
00:05:34,666 --> 00:05:37,333
They come to worship
just for the sake of it.

104
00:05:38,416 --> 00:05:40,250
[woman 3] Since you come here often,

105
00:05:41,291 --> 00:05:45,083
do you know the true legend
of the Black Hills Goddess?

106
00:05:48,416 --> 00:05:50,333
You may have heard

107
00:05:50,416 --> 00:05:54,166
she was a fishmonger's daughter
who fell in love with a prince,

108
00:05:55,625 --> 00:05:59,250
leading to a forbidden, cross-class love.

109
00:05:59,958 --> 00:06:01,833
Obstructed by the elders,

110
00:06:01,916 --> 00:06:05,291
she decided to end her life
to escape the pain.

111
00:06:06,208 --> 00:06:08,291
It became a famous true love story,

112
00:06:08,375 --> 00:06:12,333
which has inspired lovers to come here
and make prayers until today.

113
00:06:13,333 --> 00:06:14,250
But actually,

114
00:06:15,041 --> 00:06:15,958
that's not all.

115
00:06:17,500 --> 00:06:18,458
The prince

116
00:06:20,166 --> 00:06:21,708
actually had a betrothed.

117
00:06:22,375 --> 00:06:24,916
[woman 3] After he had an affair
with the Goddess,

118
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:26,666
he dumped her.

119
00:06:28,125 --> 00:06:29,250
But, of course,

120
00:06:29,333 --> 00:06:33,500
the prince couldn't escape
the wrong he had committed.

121
00:06:33,583 --> 00:06:35,083
[bells chiming]

122
00:06:35,166 --> 00:06:39,166
The Goddess returned to the prince
and his betrothed at their house.

123
00:06:39,250 --> 00:06:40,750
She conjured a rainstorm

124
00:06:40,833 --> 00:06:43,666
and used it to slash him down to the bone
like a knife.

125
00:06:43,750 --> 00:06:44,916
[man crying in pain]

126
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:49,041
All the secrets
he had hidden from her were unveiled.

127
00:06:50,625 --> 00:06:53,125
Have you ever seen fish getting scored?

128
00:06:54,625 --> 00:06:56,333
[woman 3] Long cuts on their skin?

129
00:06:57,708 --> 00:06:59,291
Both got scored to death.

130
00:06:59,375 --> 00:07:02,333
-[bells chiming]
-That is the true identity of the Goddess.

131
00:07:02,833 --> 00:07:07,291
She is the Goddess who believes
love is a matter of life and death.

132
00:07:07,791 --> 00:07:10,416
Sometimes she uses her power

133
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:14,041
to make lovers
see each other's true colors.

134
00:07:14,541 --> 00:07:17,041
Think carefully before making your wishes.

135
00:07:17,125 --> 00:07:20,916
Otherwise, you might see
what you don't want to see.

136
00:07:21,625 --> 00:07:22,833
[chuckles]

137
00:07:25,541 --> 00:07:27,208
But you already know that.

138
00:07:28,333 --> 00:07:31,208
[woman 3] You should go
and worship her now.

139
00:07:31,916 --> 00:07:33,375
[ominous music continues]

140
00:07:33,458 --> 00:07:35,166
[woman 2] We hereby vow

141
00:07:36,208 --> 00:07:38,416
in front of you, Black Hills Goddess,

142
00:07:40,041 --> 00:07:42,458
that we'll remain steadfast in our love

143
00:07:43,083 --> 00:07:45,000
and faithful to each other.

144
00:07:46,083 --> 00:07:49,208
We will not keep any problems we may have

145
00:07:50,125 --> 00:07:51,458
from each other.

146
00:07:52,875 --> 00:07:54,375
May the Goddess

147
00:07:54,875 --> 00:07:56,500
help both of us

148
00:07:57,083 --> 00:08:01,458
to be together forever.

149
00:08:01,541 --> 00:08:03,416
[chi-chi sticks rattling]

150
00:08:09,541 --> 00:08:10,583
[music stops]

151
00:08:14,041 --> 00:08:15,250
[bells chiming]

152
00:08:16,708 --> 00:08:18,708
[ominous music playing]

153
00:08:42,458 --> 00:08:44,375
[bells chiming]

154
00:08:46,625 --> 00:08:47,916
[music stops]

155
00:08:49,833 --> 00:08:51,833
-[bells chiming]
-It's all smudged.

156
00:08:52,708 --> 00:08:54,708
Let's go so we won't be home late.

157
00:08:57,875 --> 00:08:58,750
Come on.

158
00:08:59,541 --> 00:09:01,541
[ominous music playing]

159
00:09:04,583 --> 00:09:07,375
BUT THY LOVE

160
00:09:07,458 --> 00:09:09,916
SHALL BE IN DISTRESS

161
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:12,250
IF THOU HIDE

162
00:09:12,333 --> 00:09:14,833
THY PROBLEMS.

163
00:09:17,791 --> 00:09:19,833
WITHHOLD

164
00:09:19,916 --> 00:09:21,958
THY WORDS

165
00:09:22,041 --> 00:09:24,333
AND RISK

166
00:09:24,416 --> 00:09:28,375
THY LOVE'S END.

167
00:09:29,250 --> 00:09:34,041
THE VOW

168
00:09:36,166 --> 00:09:38,166
[waves swashing]

169
00:09:39,125 --> 00:09:42,791
-[music stops]
-[woman 2] It's intricate and exquisite.

170
00:09:50,666 --> 00:09:51,958
[sighs]

171
00:09:52,041 --> 00:09:53,541
[suspenseful music playing]

172
00:09:55,541 --> 00:09:56,541
[car door closes]

173
00:10:01,041 --> 00:10:02,125
[phone clicking]

174
00:10:02,625 --> 00:10:04,583
WE'RE THRILLED TO OFFER YOU...

175
00:10:04,666 --> 00:10:07,500
INBOX

176
00:10:17,958 --> 00:10:19,958
[suspenseful music continues]

177
00:10:23,750 --> 00:10:25,541
-[woman 2] Babe.
-[music stops]

178
00:10:25,625 --> 00:10:28,458
It's ten times prettier than the photos.

179
00:10:29,166 --> 00:10:31,000
-[Nat] Do you like it?
-I love it.

180
00:10:31,875 --> 00:10:33,000
[music stops]

181
00:10:33,083 --> 00:10:34,333
[birds chirping]

182
00:10:35,291 --> 00:10:36,250
Hello, Dad.

183
00:10:36,333 --> 00:10:38,500
I love what Nat did a lot, Dao.

184
00:10:38,583 --> 00:10:40,666
[Dao's dad] You never disappoint me, Nat.

185
00:10:41,541 --> 00:10:44,416
We're ready to build
a new resort in Phuket.

186
00:10:44,500 --> 00:10:48,000
Nat, I'll have you oversee the design
from start to finish.

187
00:10:48,583 --> 00:10:50,791
We'll discuss the details soon, okay?

188
00:10:52,750 --> 00:10:55,500
I have to tend to my business now.
Talk later.

189
00:10:55,583 --> 00:10:56,625
[Dao] Bye-bye, Dad.

190
00:11:05,458 --> 00:11:07,458
[melancholy music playing]

191
00:11:22,541 --> 00:11:23,583
[Dao] Hey, babe.

192
00:11:25,500 --> 00:11:27,041
It's on this day,

193
00:11:28,458 --> 00:11:30,291
